                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d158">
                <head>158. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d158fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 611.41/5–357. Secret; Priority. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName> was in Bonn for a Ministerial Meeting of the North
                        Atlantic Council, May 2–3.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bonn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-05-03T22:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1957—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 6. For Acting Secretary, <persName
                        corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RNA1"
                        >Robertson</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Selwyn Lloyd</persName>
                    told me today that he thought I should know that their Board of Trade said that
                    our China trade proposals were “no good.” I told him that we had “torn our heart
                    out” to make these proposals and I could not understand their reaction.
                        <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Lloyd</persName> said no doubt we had made a
                    political effort but there was no economic substance in it and that the items
                    that really counted were still on the embargoed list. We left it at that.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
